This problem has been taken from a contest of Hacker earth:

Problem statement:

Let there be a number n. Find largest number, x such that x is less than or equal to n
and all the digits of x are prime

Eg: If n = 1000
then x = 777


Solution: a. Iterate through the entries from 1 to N. 
		  b. Obtain all the digits in the entries
		  c. Individually check if the digits are prime.
		  d. If found true concatenate them and finally reverse the string
		  e. The last entry will always be the greatest.